properties.headline: High Wind Warning issued January 8 at 2:36AM MST until January 9 at 5:00AM MST by NWS Cheyenne WY
properties.description:
...HIGH WIND WARNING REPLACING THE HIGH WIND WATCH FOR ARLINGTON
AND BORDEAUX. GUSTY WINDS LIKELY THROUGH THURSDAY MORNING...

The National Weather Service in Cheyenne has issued a High Wind
Warning, which is in effect until 5 AM MST Thursday. The High
Wind Watch has been replaced and is no longer in effect.

* WHAT...West winds 35 to 45 mph with gusts of 60 to 65 mph
possible.

* WHERE...Bordeaux along Interstate 25 between Chugwater and
Wheatland, and Arlington and Elk Mountain along Interstate 80
between Rawlins and Laramie.

* WHEN...From 5 AM MST this morning through 5 AM MST Thursday.


* IMPACTS...Mainly to transportation. Strong cross winds can cause
blow overs especially for light and high profile vehicles. Areas
of blowing and drifting snow may reduce visibility. Use caution.
properties.instruction:
Monitor the latest forecasts and warnings for updates on this
situation. Fasten loose objects or shelter objects in a safe
location prior to the onset of winds.

A High Wind Warning means a hazardous high wind event is expected
or occurring. Sustained wind speeds of at least 40 mph or gusts
of 58 mph or more can lead to property damage.

NWSheadline: HIGH WIND WARNING IN EFFECT UNTIL 5 AM MST THURSDAY
